Step back for a moment. What you've just watched is an intelligence platform sitting on top of your source systems. Archer is the system of record for controls today; LeanIX, for applications. But the platform is loosely coupled — a different control framework or a different application catalog tomorrow becomes configuration, not rebuild. What EMS does — automatically, every cycle — is draw the org chart for compliance. Every control, every application, every ownership tie, navigable in one place. The AI surfaces what changed and what to attend to, so the Risk Manager reviews conclusions, not 200 line items. And the audit trail is the byproduct of running the system — every change time-stamped, every record immutable, every cycle preserved. The platform handles the staging, routing, and tracking. The Risk Manager's time shifts to judgment. All without the spreadsheets, manual chase, and per-cycle staging the work used to require.
